National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan had a conversation with Akiba Takeo, Secretary General of Japan's National Security Secretariat, to prepare for President's meeting with Prime Minister Kishida and discuss the ongoing situation in Russia and Ukraine. They talked about issues related to the U.S.-Japan Alliance, approaches to North Korea, China, and economic matters in the Indo-Pacific. Sullivan expressed concern about the potential for more Russian aggression in Ukraine, and they agreed on the significance of showing solidarity to Moscow and responding strongly in case of an attack.